name: antenna_quetzal
title: CA-A06 Omnidirectional Antenna
description: A simple omnidirectional antenna. Can be used for short range telecommunications or as a backup medium gain antenna.

name: antenna_tv
title: CA-A01 Ground Plane Antenna
description: A simple omnidirectional antenna for telemetry purposes.

name: barquetta
title: SSTL-150 Satellite Bus
description: A generic satellite bus for mini satellites and probes.

name: ca_DUSTC
title: CA-DUST-C Dust Sample Collector
description: The DUST-C array features an aerogel - coated collector for trapping the dust particles to return them to Earth for analysis. NOTE: heat shield and parachutes are not included.

name: ca_DUSTX
title: CA-DUST-X Cosmic Dust Counter
description: The DUST-X is an instrument that collects dust particles and provides information about their size, speed and direction.

name: ca_ELIX
title: CA-ELIX Electrostatic & Ionization Experiment
description: The ELIX is an electrostatic analyzer for analyzing the synthesis of charged particles. By employing electric and magnetic fields ELIX concentrates and separates the different particles by their mass and charge, allowing for very precise measurements of plasma density, velocity and distribution.

name: ca_ESM
title: Pioneer 10/11 Science Package
description: An integrated science package originally designed for the Pioneer 10 & 11 deep space probes. Includes a thermal control system with a thermal rejection capability of 50 Watts.

name: ca_GRS
title: CA-SCGRS Gamma Ray Spectrometer
description: The Gamma Ray Spectrometer measures the gamma ray energy generated from the planetary surfaces when these are bombarded by cosmic rays. By measuring the gamma ray energy we can determine the elemental synthesis and concentration of the soil.

name: ca_KLIR
title: CA-THEMIS Infrared Spectrometer
description: The THEMIS (Thermal Emission Imaging System) is used to measure the thermal emissions of the planetary bodies, calculate the surface temperature or even map small details of surface features. The spectrometer can also measure the wavelength of IR emissions to detect certain minerals in the soil.

name: ca_LUV
title: CA-IUVS Imaging Ultraviolet Spectrometer
description: IUVS (Imaging Ultraviolet Spectrometer) images the lower part of the UV spectrum. By doing so it can measure the global characteristics of the upper atmospheric and ionospheric layers, providing information about the synthesis, the morphology and the interactions between the solar wind and the atmosphere.

name: ca_RM01
title: CAE-RM01 RCS Thruster Block
description: An RCS thruster block for attitude control of upper stages or medium - sized spacecraft.

name: ca_RM03
title: CAE-RM03 RCS Thruster Block
description: An RCS thruster block for attitude control of upper stages or medium - sized spacecraft.

name: ca_RM04
title: CAE-RM04 RCS Thruster Block
description: An RCS thruster block for attitude control of upper stages or medium - sized spacecraft.

name: ca_RPWS
title: CA-RPWS Radio and Plasma Wave Science
description: The Radio and Plasma Wave Science (RPWS) uses sensitive wideband electric/magnetic monopole and dipole antennae to receive low frequency radio transmissions caused by trapped charged particles (cyclotron waves), electrostatic discharges and whistlers (lighting) and thermal plasma. All these sources can be used to analyze the spectrum and type of the plasma, the electron density and distribution of the magnetospheres and the various lighting effects on the lower atmospheric layers.

name: ca_SWIS
title: CA-SWIA Solar Wind Analyzer
description: The Solar Wind Analyzer (SWIA) instrument is designed specifically to detect and measure solar wind electron/ion velocity and density.

name: ca_argo-mk2-hga
title: Mariner Mars & Venus High Gain Antenna (HGA)

name: ca_argo-mk2-mast
title: Mariner Mars & Venus Low Gain Antenna (LGA)

name: ca_barometer
title: CA-SC102 Barometer
description: The SC102 measures the local atmospheric pressure.

name: ca_battery_l
title: CA-300i Battery
description: A 500 Wh capacity battery.

name: ca_battery_m
title: CA-100i Battery
description: A 170 Wh capacity battery.

name: ca_battery_s
title: CA-25i Battery
description: A 85 Wh capacity battery. Low profile for easier placement.

name: ca_fom_drogue
title: Venera Lander Drogue Parachute
description: Some Fomalhaut atmospheric entry profiles call for earlier and/or more gentle braking. For those, we've designed this massive and resilient drogue chute. Warning: This chute is not rated for low touch-down velocities. Prepare for harsh, bumpy landings (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

name: ca_fom_heatS
title: CAE-HS100 Fomalhaut Heat Shield
description: This is the bottom piece of the Fomalhaut spherical atmospheric entry shell. It is coated with a very heat-resistant ablative material to keep the stuff inside from getting cooked. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

name: ca_fom_lander
title: Venera Lander Bus
description: The CAE Planetary Science Division has produced this rugged 'metal tank', and crammed it with batteries, radiation lining, a thermometer, a camera to image the landing site, and an antenna wrapped around the top. It is designed to survive rough landings in extreme environments (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

name: ca_fom_parachute
title: Venera Lander Main Parachute
description: This part is the top cover of the Fomalhaut atmospheric entry capsule. This parachute attaches directly to the Fomalhaut lander for deployment after re-entry. It does so successfully most of the time. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

name: ca_fom_sp
title: Venera Lander Bus Solar Array
description: A small and basic solar panel angled for mounting on the Fomalhaut lander collar to provide electric recharge of the batteries (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

name: ca_jib
title: Generic 0.5 kN Thruster
description: A generic mono/bipropellant rocket motor. Can be configured within a great range of propellants. Plume configured by RealPlume.

name: ca_lahar
title: R-40 Series
description: A bipropellant rocket motor burning either MMH and MON3 (R-40A/B and R-42) or Hydrazine and MON3 (R-42DM). Used for attitude control, orbital insertion or as an apogee motor. Plume configured by RealPlume.

name: ca_landv_battery
title: Surveyor Battery Pack
description: The main battery pack of the Surveyor lunar lander. Capacity: <color=orange>3650</color> Wh.

name: ca_landv_cam_s1
title: Surveyor Landing Survey Camera
description: The main survey television camera of the Surveyor lander. The integrated mirror can be rotated by 360 degrees to create panoramas of the landing site.

name: ca_landv_core
title: Surveyor Core
description: The main assembly of the Surveyor lander. Includes a set of landing legs, attitude control system and propellant for its 3 vernier engines (sold separately). A solid fueled retro-motor is required for normal landing operations.

name: ca_landv_hga
title: Surveyor Planar Antenna and Solar Array
description: The planar high gain antenna and solar array for the Surveyor lander.

name: ca_landv_omni
title: Surveyor Omni Antenna
description: The omnidirectional low gain antenna for the Surveyor lander. Can serve as a backup for the main planar antenna.

name: ca_landv_soilScoop
title: Surveyor Soil Mechanics Surface Sampler
description: The soil mechanics surface sampler is an instrument designed to test the physical properties of the topsoil (density, porosity, resistivity) and to expose subsoil material for photography.

name: ca_landv_srm
title: STAR 37
description: The STAR 37 is a vacuum solid rocket motor, originally developed for the Surveyor lunar lander program as a braking stage. Later variants were used exclusively as apogee kick stages. Diameter: 0.93 m. Plume configured by RealPlume.

name: ca_landv_vernier
title: TD-339
description: The Vernier System as used on the Surveyor Probes. Uses storable hypergolic propellants, has infinite restarts and is not subject to ullage. Throttleable down to 30%. Historically 3 of them were used on the Surveyor probes which landed on the Moon. Diameter: [0.13 m]. Plume configured by RealPlume.

name: ca_linkor
title: Fregat-M Upper Stage
description: The Fregat is an upper stage used on the Soyuz and Zenit launch vehicles for injecting/placing payloads into low, medium or high energy orbits. It originated as a propulsion module for the Soviet Luna and Mars missions and later modified to serve as a standalone upper stage. Versions include the original Fregat, the Fregat-M with increased propellant loading and extended S5.92 nozzle, the Fregat-MT with additional propellant tanks and the Fregat-SB designed specifically for the Zenit launch vehicle family (featuring an auxiliary drop tank). Plume configured by RealPlume.

name: ca_louver_m
title: CA-TCL8 Thermal Control Louver
description: Thermal Control Louvers are heat control systems that can expel heat by exposing cooling fins and a radiator. Toggle the vents open to release heat from the spacecraft. This system has double the height and performance of the TCL4-B for better cooling. Rated heat rejection capability 100 Watts.

name: ca_louver_s
title: CA-TCL4 Thermal Control Louver
description: Thermal Control Louvers are heat control systems that can expel heat by exposing cooling fins and a radiator. Toggle the vents open to release heat from the spacecraft. This is the standard size system with a rated heat rejection capability of 40 Watts.

name: ca_louver_s2
title: CA-TCL4-B Thermal Control Louver
description: Thermal Control Louvers are heat control systems that can expel heat by exposing cooling fins and a radiator. Toggle the vents open to release heat from the spacecraft. This is an alternate, longer version of the TCL4, with a rated heat rejection capability of 50 Watts.

name: ca_magneto2
title: Triaxial Helium Vector Magnetometer
description: The magnetometer instruments are used to determine the magnitude and direction of planetary magnetic fields The long boom separates these instruments from any interference caused by magnetic elements in the probe.

name: ca_rtg2000
title: Pioneer SNAP-19 RTG
description: The SNAP-19 radioisotope thermoelectric generator as found on the Pioneer spacecraft. Developed by the Atomic Energy Commission (AEC).

name: ca_rtg3900
title: Voyager MHW-RTG
description: The Multihundred-Watt radioisotope thermoelectric generator (MHW-RTG) as found on the Voyager spacecraft.

name: ca_rtg8200
title: GPHS-RTG
description: The General-Purpose Heat Source radioisotope thermoelectric generator as found on the Ulysses and the New Horizons spacecrafts.

name: ca_rw_medium
title: RW-2A Radial Reaction Wheel Assembly
description: This reaction wheel assembly combines two RW4 high performance reaction wheels for medium size spacecraft that require precision attitude control.

name: ca_rw_small
title: RW4 Radial Reaction Wheel
description: High performance reaction wheels for precision spacecraft attitude control.

name: ca_rw_xsmall
title: RW1 Radial Reaction Wheel
description: High performance reaction wheels for precision spacecraft attitude control.

name: ca_sciBoom
title: Voyager Science Boom
description: The science boom of the Voyager deep space probe. The boom mounts Narrow and Wide field cameras for orbital survey images, as well as an Infrared and an Ultraviolet spectrometer. NOTE: Deploy the boom to keep experiments away from electromagnetic interference and radiation.

name: ca_tank_mp_s
title: CA-MT10 Propellant Tank (Pressurized)
description: A generic radially attached high pressure propellant tank for use on upper stages or small - sized spacecraft.

name: ca_telescope_a
title: CA-HiRISE Telescope
description: The High Resolution Imaging Science Experiment (HiRISE) is a Cassegrain - type visible spectrum telescope and one of the biggest to ever fly in a deep space probe. With it's high resolution capability it can acquire high definition color surface images.

name: ca_torekkaPM
title: Voyager Propulsion Module
description: The Voyager Propulsion Module is powered by a modified version of the STAR-37E solid rocket motor. It includes a Reaction Control System (RCS) for controlling the attitude of the Voyager stack for the duration of the SRM injection burn. Attach it to the bottom of the Voyager truss adapter.

name: ca_trident
title: Bi-Propellant Apogee Engine
description: A cluster of three 400N Bi-Propellant Apogee Motors. Designed for apogee orbit injection of geostationary satellites and for trajectory and planetary orbit maneuvers of deep space probes. Plume configured by RealPlume.

name: ca_vor_comm
title: CAE-A03 Vorona Communication Array
description: Vorona's Comm Array mounts dual conic antennae for short range, low-gain communication. The system also has a mount for a high-gain dish, designed for the Vorona CAE-102 dish (Sold separately). (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

name: ca_vor_core
title: 4MV Spacecraft Bus
description: The Vorona probe system is designed to work in tandem with a Fomalhaut lander to conduct simultaneous orbital/surface science. It packs batteries, avionics, and monopropellant in a very rugged case. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

name: ca_vor_dish
title: CAE-102 Vorona Dish Antenna
description: The Vorona dish has a powerful transmitter for its size, that should allow a fair bit of range in communication in the inner solar system; whether you want it to or not. (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

name: ca_vor_engine
title: KTDU-425A
description: A gas generator hypergolic vacuum engine designed for use in the 3MV, 4MV and 5MV spacecraft buses of the Mars and Venera probes.

name: ca_vor_mptank
title: CAE-MT12 Propellant Tank (Pressurized)
description: A generic, radially attached high pressure propellant tank.

name: ca_vor_sep1
title: CAE-D13-F Stack Decoupler
description: Takes two pieces for connect together and after not when you want to not have together more. Many quality part made in Kaiwan! (PART NOT SUPPORTED BY RP-0 OR RO)

name: ca_vor_tank
title: 4MV-1/2 Spacecraft Bus Propellant Tank
description: The main pressurized propellant storage compartment of the 4MV-1/2 spacecraft bus.

name: dish_L
title: Voyager 1 & 2 Parabolic Antenna
description: The main parabolic telecommunications antenna of the Voyager spacecraft.

name: dish_S
title: Ulysses Parabolic Antenna
description: The main parabolic telecommunications antenna of the Ulysses spacecraft.

name: dish_deploy_S
title: CA-A10 Folding Dish Antenna
description: The CA-A10 provides the advantages of a dish antenna without cluttering the front of your spacecraft. Electric servos fold the dish close to the hull during launch.

name: dish_deploy_S2
title: CA-AD1-R Folding Dish Antenna
description: A medium gain directional antenna for short range, high bandwidth communications.

name: dish_quetzal
title: Pioneer 10 & 11 Parabolic Antenna
description: The main parabolic telecommunications antenna of the Pioneer spacecraft.

name: dish_tatsujin
title: MAVEN Parabolic Antenna
description: The main parabolic telecommunications antenna of the the Mars Atmosphere and Volatile EvolutioN (MAVEN) spacecraft.

name: quetzal
title: Pioneer 10/11 Core
description: Avionics and control unit for the Pioneer deep space probes.

name: sp_express_a
title: Venus Express Solar Array Wing (SAW)
description: A solar array wing used on the Venus Express spacecraft. 2.88 m2.

name: sp_express_b
title: Mars Express Solar Array Wing (SAW)
description: A solar array wing used on the Mars Express spacecraft. 5.76 m2.

name: sp_mariner_a
title: CA-E100 1x2 Solar Panel
description: A solar array wing, similar to the one used by the Mariner Venus spacecrafts, featuring increased power generation efficiency. 2.43 m2.

name: sp_mariner_b
title: CA-E100-SPV 1x2 Solar Panel
description: A solar array wing, similar to the one used by the Mariner Mars spacecrafts. Includes Solar Pressure Vanes for finer attitude control. 2.34 m2.

name: sp_maven
title: MAVEN Solar Array Wing (SAW)
description: A solar array wing used on the Mars Atmosphere and Volatile EvolutioN (MAVEN) spacecraft. Includes a three - axis magnetometer. 12 m2.

name: sp_odyssey_a
title: Mars Odyssey Solar Array Wing (SAW)
description: A very efficient Gallium Arsenide (GaAs) photovoltaic array with an eccentric pivot point to minimize it's stowed footprint. 5.88 m2

name: sp_odyssey_b
title: CA-E200B 1x2 Solar Panel
description: An alternate photovoltaic system with vastly improved clearance, based on our award-winning E200 Series. 5.46 m2.

name: tatsujin
title: LM-DS Generic Spacecraft Bus
description: A general purpose spacecraft bus. Example uses include the Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter (MRO), the Mars Atmosphere and Volatile EvolutioN (MAVEN), and the OSIRIS-REx missions.

name: torekka
title: Voyager Core
description: Avionics and control unit for the Voyager deep space probes.
